# Design Token Quick Reference (Tailwind v4)

**Use with the Component Conversion Playbook** (`.cursor/rules/component-conversion-playbook.mdc`) when converting or creating components.

**All design tokens are defined in `app/globals.css` using the `@theme` directive.**

Use these exact class names when styling components. NEVER use arbitrary values.

## Breakpoints (Mobile-First)

Tailwind uses **min-width** breakpoints. Base classes = mobile, breakpoint prefixes override for larger screens.

| Prefix | Range | Description |
|--------|-------|-------------|
| **(none)** | 0-480px | **Mobile (base)** - no prefix needed |
| `md:` | 481px+ | Tablet and up |
| `lg:` | 1025px+ | Desktop and up |
| `xl:` | 1601px+ | Full width and up |

**Key Concept:** Styles cascade UP. A `md:` class applies to tablet, desktop, AND fullWidth unless overridden.

**Usage Pattern:**
```jsx
// Mobile base, then add breakpoints for what CHANGES
className="flex-col w-107 gap-7.5 md:w-236 lg:(flex-row w-326)"

// If value is same across all breakpoints, just use base
className="gap-6"  // No prefixes needed if gap is always 24px
```

**Converting styled-components:**
- `${media.mobile}` → base (no prefix)
- `${media.tablet}` → `md:`
- Desktop (base) → `lg:`
- `${media.fullWidth}` → `xl:`

